  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). A screening sensitivity study was performed informally during model development to examine the effect of mesh density and blood viscosity on the relative hemolysis index; results were consistent across all tested parameter ranges and supported the chosen modelling assumptions. This screening activity informed factor ratings but was not elevated to a formal sensitivity analysis node in the credibility package.",
