    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 7 assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for Model Risk Level 2. Six factors are appropriately scoped out per the MRL 2 assessment matrix. Validation evidence demonstrates CFD predictions of relative hemolysis index within 12% of experimental values across the COU operating envelope, satisfying the RH < 1 acceptance criterion at the worst-case operating point. A screening sensitivity study conducted during model development confirmed that hemolysis predictions are stable with respect to mesh density and blood viscosity perturbations, further supporting the adequacy of the modelling approach. The credibility package is judged sufficient to support the regulatory decision for this Class II CPB device.",
